I'm glad you liked the revision. "Wove" conveys integration and subtle craftsmanship, which works well for showing that you blended these perspectives thoughtfully into your research. However, if you want a more active or vivid image, you could consider alternatives like "infused," "integrated," or even "anchored"—each offers a slightly different nuance. For example: 

"I integrated these international perspectives into my MSc research..." feels straightforward and strong; 

"I infused my MSc research with these international perspectives..." gives an energetic, almost creative connotation; 

"I anchored my MSc research in these international perspectives..." suggests grounding your entire approach in what you learned overseas.
